      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's the official line, but \"telemetry limitations\" is a pretty convenient excuse for why certain specific frames or signal bursts go missing in the public datasets. if it was just bugs, why do the gaps always happen during the exact windows where the landing module is approaching the lunar surface? it feels more like a controlled redaction than a technical glitch. if we look past the \"official\" explanations, are there any specific redacted mission logs or non-standard orbital data reports that supposedly exist but aren't in the main public archives?",
